§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ For a nonzero $b ∈ 𝗥^n$ and $β ∈ 𝗥$ the sets
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ \Set*{x ∈ 𝗥^n}{\ip{x,b} ≤ β}, \quad \Set*{x ∈
        𝗥^n}{\ip{x,b} ≥ β}, ⦉
    ⦉
    are ❬closed halfspaces❭ and the sets
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ \Set*{x ∈ 𝗥^n}{\ip{x,b} ≤ β}, \quad \Set*{x ∈
        𝗥^n}{\ip{x,b} ≥ β}, ⦉
    ⦉

    ‖ are ❬open halfspaces❭. ⦉⦉
⦉

¶ ⦊
  ‖ Each of these is nonempty and convex. ⦉

  ‖ As with hyperplanes, the same four sets appear if one uses
    $λ β$ and $λ b$ above, so the halfspaces depend only on
    the hyperplane $H = \Set*{x}{\ip{x}{b} = β}$. ⦉
⦉

